article.headline: Terion Stewart scores 3 touchdowns to highlight Bowling Green's 41-14 victory over Akron
article.description: — Terion Stewart ran for 131 yards and scored three touchdowns, leading Bowling Green to a 41-14 victory over Akron on Saturday.
article.linkText: Terion Stewart scores 3 touchdowns to highlight Bowling Green's 41-14 victory over Akron

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Drake Anderson scores 4-yard rushing TD) 2023/10/21 ESHEET

article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- — Terion Stewart ran for 131 yards and scored three touchdowns, leading Bowling Green to a 41-14 victory over Akron on Saturday. A short TD run by Stewart gave the Falcons a 10-7 lead in the second quarter. He added two more scores as Bowling Green broke open the game with a 21-point third quarter. Connor Bazelak's 36-yard scoring pass gave the Falcons a 34-7 lead in the third quarter and backup QB Camden Orth made it 41-7 when he hit Abdul-Fatai Ibrahim for an 8-yard score in the fourth quarter. Akron got touchdown runs of 13 yards from Lorenzo Lingard in the first quarter and 4 yards from Drake Anderson late in the fourth. Stewart led a ground game that churned out 214 yards for the Falcons (4-4, 2-2 Mid-American Conference). Bazelak was 6-for-11 passing for 69 yards and Orth was 2-for-3 for 14 yards. Each QB had one touchdown pass. Jeff Undercuffler Jr. completed 22 of 39 passes for 234 yards for the Zips (1-7, 0-4). He was intercepted twice. ------ Get alerts on the latest AP Top 25 poll throughout the season.
